title: Values of Generalized Continued Fractions with Polynomial Terms
tag: math
---

Intended to be found by search engines when a value is known but the generalized continued fraction is unknown.
These are the first 36,937 converging values with polynomials of lowest total score.
Polynomial score is equal to its degree plus the sum of absolute values of its coefficients.

$$
x = b_0 + \cfrac {a_1} {b_1 + \cfrac {a_2} {b_2 + \ddots}}
$$

The 'Terms' column is the number of continued fraction terms needed to calculate
the value to the precision shown.
